  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Arrays\n",
    "Arrays are best created using numpy array and plots using matplotlib."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "m = array([[ 11., 12, 13, 14 ],\n",
    "           [ 21, 22, 23, 24 ],\n",
    "           [ 31, 32, 33, 34 ]])\n",
    "print(m)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "where a is 4-by-4 matrix of double numbers, due to the fact than ```11.``` is a real number."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Array multiplication\n",
    "Arrays can be multiplied easily element by element"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true,
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "fragment"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "b = 3.0 * m"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "A scalar multiplication is applied to each element of the array."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Sequences\n",
    "An array sequence can be created with ```arange```. Array indexing starts at 0."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": true
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "a=arange(1,5)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
    "## Slicing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "collapsed": false
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "a[1:] #from 1 till the end, (starts at zero)\n",
    "m[:,0] = 99 # first column\n",
    "m[-2:,] #indexing backwards is possible"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "slideshow": {
     "slide_type": "slide"
    }
   },
   "source": [
